.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
Grouping compounds can contain several other widgets. 
.PP
They display a frame and optionally a title.
.SH "Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "\fBsgWidget\fP * sgNewGroupSplitted (\fBsgWidget\fP * based, \fBsgEdge\fP edge, int pixels, const char * caption)"
.PP
Creates a new group widget by splitting another. 
.PP
\fBParameters:\fP
.RS 4
\fIbased\fP widget which we'll split 
.br
\fIedge\fP at which edge «based» will be splitted 
.br
\fIpixels\fP how many pixels to split off 
.br
\fIcaption\fP group caption
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns:\fP
.RS 4
pointer to the newly created group or NULL on error.
.RE
.PP

.SS "void sgSubGroup (\fBsgWidget\fP * group, \fBsgWidget\fP * add, \fBsgEdge\fP edge, \fBsgAlign\fP align)"
.PP
Adds a widget to a group by splitting its dimensions from the 'splitted' rectangle, which has initially the dimensions of the body. 
.PP
\fBParameters:\fP
.RS 4
\fIgroup\fP the group we're gonna add a widget to 
.br
\fIadd\fP the widget which is added 
.br
\fIedge\fP the edge at which we split the 'splitted' rectangle 
.br
\fIalign\fP how we align the widget inside the rect we splitted off
.RE
.PP

.SS "int sgSetGroupImage (\fBsgWidget\fP * group, SDL_Surface * image, \fBsgAlign\fP align)"
.PP
Sets the background image of a group. 
.PP
\fBParameters:\fP
.RS 4
\fIgroup\fP The group that will have its background changed 
.br
\fIimage\fP Image data of the new background 
.br
\fIalign\fP How the image will be aligned inside the group
.RE
.PP

.SS "Uint16 sgSetGroupTab (\fBsgWidget\fP * group, Uint16 offset)"
.PP
Modifies the caption rectangle so the group can be used in a tab widget. 
.PP
\fBParameters:\fP
.RS 4
\fIgroup\fP The group which is beeing modified 
.br
\fIoffset\fP Offset at which the caption starts from the left
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns:\fP
.RS 4
Width of the caption rectangle (offset + return value = offset to the next tabgroup)
.RE
.PP

